import pandas as pd
import csv
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from datetime import datetime
import numpy as np

stat = input("What statistic would you like to analyze today? Games Played, Points, Assists, Rebounds, Steals, Blocks, Field Goal %, or 3 Point %?")

plt.title(str(stat) + " of each Atlanta Hawks Player")

if stat == "Games Played":
    stat = 1
elif stat == "Points":
    stat = 2
elif stat == "Assists":
    stat = 3
elif stat == "Rebounds":
    stat = 4
elif stat == "Steals":
    stat = 5
elif stat == "Blocks":
    stat = 6
elif stat == "Field Goal %":
    stat = 7
elif stat == "3 Point %":
    stat = 8

data = pd.read_csv('files/hawks.csv')

graph = input("Would you like this data as a Bar Graph or a Pie Chart?")

if graph == "Bar Graph":
    x_pos = np.arange(len(data))
    df = pd.DataFrame(data)
    X = list(df.iloc[:, 0])
    Y = list(df.iloc[:, stat])
    plt.bar(X, Y, color='g')
    plt.xlabel("Players")
    plt.ylabel("Statistics")
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)

elif graph == "Pie Chart":
    plt.pie(data.iloc[:, stat], labels=list(data.iloc[:, 0]))
    plt.axis('equal')

plt.show()

from datetime import datetime
import numpy as np

stat = input("What statistic would you like to analyze today? Games Played, Points, Assists, Rebounds, Steals, Blocks, Field Goal %, or 3 Point %?")

plt.title(str(stat) + " of each New York Knicks Player")

if stat == "Games Played":
    stat = 1
elif stat == "Points":
    stat = 2
elif stat == "Assists":
    stat = 3
elif stat == "Rebounds":
    stat = 4
elif stat == "Steals":
    stat = 5
elif stat == "Blocks":
    stat = 6
elif stat == "Field Goal %":
    stat = 7
elif stat == "3 Point %":
    stat = 8

data = pd.read_csv('files/knicks.csv')

graph = input("Would you like this data as a Bar Graph or a Pie Chart?")

if graph == "Bar Graph":
    x_pos = np.arange(len(data))
    df = pd.DataFrame(data)
    X = list(df.iloc[:, 0])
    Y = list(df.iloc[:, stat])
    plt.bar(X, Y, color='g')
    plt.xlabel("Players")
    plt.ylabel("Statistics")
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)

elif graph == "Pie Chart":
    plt.pie(data.iloc[:, stat], labels=list(data.iloc[:, 0]))
    plt.axis('equal')

plt.show()
